tButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-craft-evolution-items-anime-saga.jpg?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Preview of the Craft menu in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eYou can craft evolution items at the Craft NPC using materials found in the Story, Raid, and Gold Shop.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cp data-characters=\"275\" data-current-count=\"575\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYou can craft evolution items\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eat the\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eCraft \u003c/strong\u003e(Majin Buu) \u003cstrong\u003eNPC in the main lobby\u003c/strong\u003e. To craft an evolution item, you first need to collect some specific materials and a bit of Gold. \u003cstrong\u003eYou can farm most of these materials by doing Raids\u003c/strong\u003e, while some are also available at the \u003cstrong\u003eGold Shop\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"h-farming-materials-in-raids\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003eFarming Materials in Raids\u003c/h3\u003e    \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b1fc6\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\" data-current-count=\"300\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/how-to-start-raids-anime-saga.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Preview of the Play menu in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eThe Raid stays open for 15 minutes, starting with each hour. After 15 minutes, it goes on a 45-minute cooldown.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cp data-characters=\"254\" data-current-count=\"554\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003eYou unlock Raids when you reach \u003cstrong\u003eplayer level 25\u003c/strong\u003e. From then on, you can easily farm materials needed for evolution items in them. \u003cstrong\u003eRaids open up every hour at XX:00\u003c/strong\u003e (1:00, 2:00, etc.), \u003cstrong\u003eand they stay open for 15 minutes before going on a 45-minute cooldown\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cfigure data-current-count=\"0\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003e \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b26c7\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-id=\"1028512\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-raid-white-whale-boss.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"A player fighting the White Wale Raid boss in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRaid bosses deal a lot of damage, but you can respawn even if your whole party wipes.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b2d11\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-id=\"1028515\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-raid-rewards.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Preview of the Raid rewards menu in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDepending on how much damage you dealt, you will gain a certain amount of Gold, Gems, and various materials.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cp data-characters=\"417\" data-current-count=\"417\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003eWhen you enter a Raid, \u003cstrong\u003eyou have 15 minutes to deal as much damage as you can to the boss\u003c/strong\u003e within it. With each \u003cstrong\u003edamage threshold\u003c/strong\u003e you reach, \u003cstrong\u003eyou get an additional set of rewards\u003c/strong\u003e. Even though up to eight players can join the same Raid, the damage dealt to the boss isn’t shared between them. However, \u003cstrong\u003eteaming up with others has its benefits\u003c/strong\u003e, as your \u003cstrong\u003eUnit’s damage increases with more players\u003c/strong\u003e in the same Raid.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch4 id=\"h-where-to-spend-raid-tickets\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003eWhere to Spend Raid Tickets\u003c/h4\u003e    \u003cfigure data-current-count=\"0\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003e \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b3614\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-id=\"1028514\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-raid-shop-npc-location.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Location of the Raid Shop NPC in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTalk to the Rem and Ram NPCs in the lobby to spend your Raid tokens.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b3cab\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-id=\"1028513\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-raid-ticket-shop.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Preview of the Raid Shop stock in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYou can use Tickets to buy Units and reroll consumables from the Raid Shop.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cp data-characters=\"221\" data-current-count=\"221\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003eWhen you complete a Raid, you will get a certain number of Tickets as a reward. You can spend these Tickets at the \u003cstrong\u003eRaid Shop NPCs\u003c/strong\u003e to purchase \u003cstrong\u003eTrait and Stat rerolls\u003c/strong\u003e, as well as some very powerful \u003cstrong\u003elimited Units\u003c/strong\u003e, like Remu.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"h-buying-materials-and-food-at-the-gold-shop\" data-injectable=\"false\"\u003eBuying Materials and Food at the Gold Shop\u003c/h3\u003e    \u003cfigure data-wp-context=\"{\u0026#34;imageId\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;68292bd3b44c5\u0026#34;}\" data-wp-interactive=\"core/image\" data-current-count=\"521\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"619\" data-wp-class--hide=\"state.isContentHidden\" data-wp-class--show=\"state.isContentVisible\" data-wp-init=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async--click=\"actions.showLightbox\" data-wp-on-async--load=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" data-wp-on-async-window--resize=\"callbacks.setButtonStyles\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-gold-shop-materials.webp?resize=1200%2C619\" alt=\"Preview of the Gold Shop stock that contains materials needed to craft evolution items for certain units in the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eThe Gold Shop refreshes every 12 hours, and you can buy randomly selected materials from it.\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e    \u003cp data-characters=\"460\" data-current-count=\"460\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003eSuppose you are missing some materials to craft an evolution item for one of your Units. In that case, \u003cstrong\u003eyou can buy those occasionally at the Gold Shop\u003c/strong\u003e. Keep in mind that the \u003cstrong\u003eGold Shop stock refreshes every 12 hours\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003enot all items are available from it at once\u003c/strong\u003e. Instead, a random selection is in stock. All Rare and Epic materials are easily farmed in Raids. Thus, I suggest you \u003cstrong\u003epurchase only Legendary and Mythic materials as they have very low drop rates\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cfigure data-found-rows=\"14\" data-current-count=\"860\" data-injectable=\"true\"\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth data-align=\"center\"\u003eMaterial\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth data-align=\"center\"\u003eShop cost\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth data-align=\"center\"\u003eObtainable from\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth data-align=\"center\"\u003eNeeded for\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/anime-saga-demon-blood-food.png?resize=100%2C100\" alt=\"Demon Blood food from the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cmark\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e400 Gold\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/mark\u003e \u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cmark\u003eRed Light District Story\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cmark\u003eFan (Doma)\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/screws-material-anime-saga.png?w=1200\" alt=\"Screws material from the Anime Saga Roblox experience.\"/\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cmark\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e1,060 Gold\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cmark\u003eRaids\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cmark\u003ePochita (Chainsaw)\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr/\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cmark\u003eWeaponsZid (Zid)\u003c/mark\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd data-align=\"center\"\u003e\u003cimg data-recalc-dims=\"1\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.escapistmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/milk-material-anime-saga.png?w=1200\" alt=\"Milk material from t